"Bräuning A., Mantwill B.","Summer temperature and summer monsoon history on the Tibetan plateau during the last 400 years recorded by tree rings",2004,"Geophysical Research Letters","31","24",,"1","4",,,10.1029/2004GL020793,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-14544295714&partnerID=40&md5=31f184bf3c6696044b30f18f1406ef3b","Institute of Geography, Azenbergstrasse 12, D-70174 Stuttgart, Germany","Bräuning, A., Institute of Geography, Azenbergstrasse 12, D-70174 Stuttgart, Germany; Mantwill, B., Institute of Geography, Azenbergstrasse 12, D-70174 Stuttgart, Germany","Global circulation models predict an increase of summer monsoon precipitation in High Asia as a consequence of global warming. The shortness of available meteorological records requires the reconstruction of past climate variability. However, high-resolution climate proxy records from the Tibetan plateau are scarce and of limited spatial representativeness. Here we present first evidence of increased summer monsoon intensity from the Tibetan plateau based on reconstructions of late summer (August and September) temperature and rainfall from a network of 22 maximum latewood density (MLD) chronologies of high-elevation conifer sites. After 1980, a decrease in MLD points to an increase of Indian summer monsoon activity (in southern, Tibet unprecedented during the past 350 years. Copyright 2004 by the American Geophysical Union.","1620 Global change: Climate dynamics (3309); 3344 Meteorology and atmospheric dynamics: Paleoclimatology; 3354 Meteorology and atmospheric dynamics: Precipitation (1854); 4221 Oceanography: General: Dendrochronology; 9320 Information related to geographic region: Asia","Forestry; Global warming; Meteorology; Rain; Climate variability; Summer monsoon; Summer temperature; Tibetan plateau; Climatology; dendroclimatology; Holocene; monsoon; paleoclimate; summer; Meteorology; Rain; Tibet; Trees; Asia; China; Eastern Hemisphere; Eurasia; Far East; Qinghai-Xizang Plateau; World",,,,,,"Aggarwal, P.K., Fröhlich, K., Kulkarni, K.M., Gourcy, L.L., Stable isotope evidence for moisture sources in the Asian summer monsoon under present and past climate regimes (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett., 31 (8), pp. L08203. , doi:10.1029/2004GL019911; Briffa, K.R., Schweingruber, F.H., Jones, P.D., Osborn, T.J., Shiyatov, S.G., Vaganov, A., Reduced sensitivity of recent tree-growth to temperature at high northern latitude (1998) Nature, 393, pp. 678-682; Briffa, K.R., Jones, P.D., Schweingruber, F.H., Osborn, T.J., Influence of volcanic eruptions on Northern Hemisphere summer temperature over the last 600 years (1998) Nature, 393, pp. 450-455; Briffa, K.R., Osborn, T.J., Schweingruber, F.H., Harris, I.C., Jones, P.D., Shiyatov, S.G., Vaganov, E.A., Low-frequency temperature variations from a northern tree ring density network (2001) J. Geophys. Res., 106, pp. 2929-2941; Briffa, K.R., Tree-ring width and density data around the Northern Hemisphere: Part 1, Local and regional climate signals (2002) Holocene, 12, pp. 737-757; Collins, M., Osborn, T.J., Tett, S.F.B., Briffa, K.R., Schweingruber, F.H., A comparison of the variability of a climate model with paleotemperature estimates from a network of tree-ring densities (2002) J. Clim., 15, pp. 1497-1515; Cook, E.R., Kairiukstis, L.A., (1990) Methods of Dendrochronology, , (Eds.) Springer, New York; Cook, E.R., Briffa, K.R., Meko, D.M., Graybill, D.A., Funkhouser, G., The 'segment length curse' in long tree-ring chronology development for palaeoclimatic studies (1995) Holocene, 5, pp. 229-237; Cook, E.R., Krusic, P.J., Jones, P.D., Dendroclimatic signals in long tree-ring chronologies from the Himalayas of Nepal (2003) Int. J. Climatol., 23, pp. 63-79; Fritts, H.C., (1976) Tree Rings and Climate, p. 567. , Elsevier, New York; Jacoby, G.C., D'Arrigo, R.D., Tree ring width and density evidence of climatic and potential forest change in Alaska (1995) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 9, pp. 227-234; Körner, C., A re-assess